<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-17T00:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-17T00:35:00-05:00" n="577" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9111/642: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-17T09:00:00+03:25">January 17, 1938—9
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5. Department’s 62, December 23, 7 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d577fn2"><ref target="frus1937v02#pg_727"><hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 727</ref>.</note> In conversation with
                                the Prime Minister<note n="3" xml:id="d577fn3">Mahmud Djam.</note>
                                yesterday he assured me that he was making every effort to have the
                                Legation in Washington reopened.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>